Car Racing Game in C++

Description:
This is a simple console-based car racing game developed in C++ using the Windows console API. The player controls a car that moves left or right to avoid obstacles (enemy cars) while aiming to survive as long as possible and achieve the highest score.

Features:

  Console-based gameplay
  
  Smooth movement and enemy generation
  
  Collision detection
  
  Score tracking
  
  Game over and restart options
  
  Instructions menu

How to Play:
  
  Start the game by running the compiled executable.
  
  Use the following keys to control the car:
  
      Press 'a' to move left.
      
      Press 'd' to move right.
      
      Press 'ESC' to exit the game.
  
  Avoid collisions with enemy cars.
  
  The game ends when a collision occurs, and the final score is displayed.
